 UI Test and API test in Playwrite 
## Reports

folder: test-results
## Get Started

### Setup:

1. Clone or download the project
2. Extract and open in the VS-Code
3. `npm i` to install the dependencies
4. `npx playwright install` to install the browsers
5. `npm run test` to execute the tests


### Folder structure
0. `src\pages` -> All the page (UI screen)
1. `src\test\features` -> write your features here
2. `src\test\steps` -> Your step definitions goes here
3. `src\hooks\hooks.ts` -> Browser setup and teardown logic
4. `src\hooks\pageFixture.ts` -> Simple way to share the page objects to steps
5. `src\test-result` -> To generate the report
6. `cucumber.json` -> One file to do all the magic
7. `package.json` -> Contains all the dependencies


### Performance Test in Gatling
1. go to the gatling folder
2. run the command ` npx gatling run --typescript --simulation APIBanking`
3. check the report in the `/target/gatling/results` folder

4. run the command ` npx gatling run --typescript --simulation banking`
5. check the report in the `/target/gatling/results` folder